THE boyfriend of a murdered cop had allegedly pointed a gun at her and threatened to kill her in the past. Constable Thandiwe Mavaneni (33) from Mpumalanga kasi in Hammarsdale, west of Durban, was shot on Wednesday, allegedly by her lover after a fight. Her sister Hloniphile Mkholokotho (37) yesterday told Daily Sun that towards the end of last year, Thandiwe’s boyfriend threatened to shoot her after an argument. “I warned her not to take that incident lightly because one day it could turn ugly. I think she thought it was a one time thing because they continued dating.” on Wednesday that her sister had died in hospital after being shot. She said she was happy the suspect was arrested shortly after the shooting. Hloniphile said the suspect was a tenderpreneur and the family learned of his relationship with her sister in 2017. KZN police spokeswoman Colonel Thembeka Mbele said a case of murder was opened at Mpumalanga Police Station. “The police arrested a 26-year-old suspect after Mavaneni was shot and wounded after a domestic dispute. “She sustained multiple gunshot wounds and was taken to hospital, where she was declared dead on arrival. “A firearm was seized and will be sent for ballistics tests.” Mbele said the suspect would be charged with murder and was expected to appear in the Mpumalanga Magistrates Court today.